63. 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD892F0ED391368FCA2" authority="(Candolle ex Colladon 1816: 8) Irwin &amp; Barneby (1982: 181)" authorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityPageNumber="181" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Candolle ex Colladon" baseAuthorityPageNumber="8" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[178,1109,844,871]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macranthera">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892F0ED3916AAFCA2" bold="true" box="[178,407,844,871]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Senna macranthera</emphasis>
(Candolle ex Colladon 1816: 8) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD8914AED381368FCA2" author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[776,1109,845,871]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" pagination="1 - 918" refId="ref21480" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae - Tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 918." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby (1982: 181)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. (
<figureCitation id="13492A74FF9DFFD8962AED38123EFCA2" box="[1128,1283,845,871]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="23.[136,229,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[267,1319,190,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-18@23.[267,1319,190,1482]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 8. A and B: Senegalia polyphylla: A. branch with inflorescence; B. nectary; C: Senegalia tucumanensis, inflorescence; D: Senegalia velutina, inflorescence; E and F: Senna macranthera: E: branch with inflorescence; F: flower; G and H: Senna obtusifolia: G: branch with inflorescence; H: flower; I and J: Senna occidentalis: I: branch with inflorescence; J: flower; K and L: Sesbania virgata: K. flowers; L: branch with fruit. (A–J; L Rauber CR 2018; K Wink, JG 2019)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424842/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Fig. 8E and F</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368657AFF9DFFD892CAEDF81398FB21" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892CAEDF814F7FC2B" blockId="27.[136,1451,909,1253]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892CAEDF81619FC62" bold="true" box="[136,292,909,935]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Distribution:</emphasis>
It occurs from 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD8939DEDF8156FFC62" box="[479,594,909,935]" name="Venezuela" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
to southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD890ABEDF81410FC62" box="[745,813,909,935]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD8917DEDF814DDFC62" author="Queiroz, L. P." box="[831,992,909,935]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" refId="ref22748" refString="Queiroz, L. P. (2009) Leguminosas da Caatinga. Universidade Estadual de Feira de Santana / Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew / Associacao Plantas do Nordeste, Feira de Santana." type="book" year="2009">Queiroz 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and in 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD89604EDF813B7FC62" box="[1094,1162,909,935]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it occurs in states of all regions, though in the South only in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F813FF9DFFD890E3EDC515D0FC0F" box="[673,749,944,970]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Paraná</collectingRegion>
and in the North only in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F813FF9DFFD896C5EDC513CEFC0F" box="[1159,1267,944,970]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD89740EDC517F8FC2B" author="Flora do Brasil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" refId="ref20723" refString="Flora do Brasil (2020) under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / (accessed 10 August 2019)" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD8972AEDC51296FC0F" box="[1384,1451,944,970]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In ParNa Iguaçu it occurs in the Foz do Iguaçu and Céu Azul areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFED8313B5FBD4" blockId="27.[136,1451,909,1253]" box="[189,1160,1014,1041]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFED831689FBD5" bold="true" box="[189,436,1014,1040]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Reproductive period</emphasis>
: In ParNa Iguaçu it was found in flower in February and March.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFEA6F16E2FBBF" blockId="27.[136,1451,909,1253]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFEA6F16C4FBF1" bold="true" box="[189,505,1050,1076]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Diagnostic characteristics:</emphasis>
The genus is recognized by its androecium with only seven fertile stamens and by the indehiscent fruit, 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD8930CEA4B16C1FB92" authorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Candolle ex Colladon" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[334,508,1085,1112]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macranthera">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD8930CEA4B16C1FB92" box="[334,508,1085,1112]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">S. macranthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from the other species by its arboreal habit and pinnate leaves with only two pairs of leaflets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFEAF616D2FB58" blockId="27.[136,1451,909,1253]" box="[189,495,1155,1181]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFEAF6165AFB58" bold="true" box="[189,359,1155,1181]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Conservation:</emphasis>
Native-NE.
</paragraph>
